// Kodex Manager
// Manages a project knowledge base with SQLite metadata and Markdown content files.

Each project gets a .collab/kodex/ directory: a SQLite database (kodex.db) for metadata,
access logs, flags, and analytics; and a topics/ subdirectory where each topic has its
own folder with conceptual.md, technical.md, files.md, related.md, and diagrams.md.
A draft workflow allows AI-generated content to be staged in a topic/draft/ subdirectory
before being approved (promoted to live) or rejected (deleted).
The database is opened lazily on first use. A module-level Map provides one KodexManager
instance per project path.

FUNCTION KodexManager.constructor(projectPath)                                     EXPORT
  Set paths for kodexDir (.collab/kodex), topicsDir, and dbPath.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.ensureInitialized() -> Database
  IF database is already open, return it.
  Create kodexDir and topicsDir if they don't exist. Open SQLite, run CREATE TABLE IF NOT
  EXISTS for all schema tables and indexes, and return the database.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.listTopics() -> TopicMetadata[]
  Query all topics ordered by updated_at descending. Map rows to TopicMetadata objects.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.getTopic(name, includeContent) -> Topic | null
  Look up by exact name first, then scan all topics' aliases arrays for a match.
  IF not found, log the miss and return null.
  Log access using the actual topic name (not the alias). IF includeContent is false,
  return metadata with empty content fields. Otherwise read and return full content.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.createTopic(name, title, content, createdBy) -> Draft
  Write all content sections into a draft/ subdirectory. Insert or update the topics row
  with has_draft=1. Clean up missing_topics records and auto-resolve open "missing" flags
  for this topic. Return a Draft object.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.updateTopic(name, content, reason) -> Draft
  Verify the topic exists. Merge provided fields with the current live content.
  Write the merged content to the draft/ subdirectory. Set has_draft=1. Return a Draft object.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.directUpdateTopic(name, content, reason) -> { updated, flagId }
  Merge provided fields with current content and write directly to live files (no draft).
  Clear verification fields on the topics row. Create a "needs-review" flag (deduplicated).
  Return { updated: true }.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.directCreateTopic(name, title, content, reason) -> { created }
  Write content directly to live files. Insert topic with confidence="medium".
  Clean up missing_topics records and auto-resolve open "missing" flags.
  Create a "needs-review" flag (deduplicated). Return { created: true }.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.deleteTopic(name) -> void
  Remove the topic's directory from disk. Delete the topics row and all flags for the topic.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.verifyTopic(name, verifiedBy) -> void
  Set verified=1, verified_at, verified_by, and confidence="high" on the topics row.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.addAlias(topicName, alias) -> void
  Verify the topic exists. Throw if alias already present. Append alias to the stored JSON
  aliases array and persist.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.removeAlias(topicName, alias) -> void
  Verify the topic exists. Throw if alias not found. Filter out the alias and persist.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.listDrafts() -> Draft[]
  Query all topics with has_draft=1. Read draft content from each topic's draft/ directory.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.listDraftsSummary() -> { topicName, title, createdAt }[]
  Return lightweight summary rows for topics with pending drafts, sorted by updated_at.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.getDraft(topicName) -> Draft | null
  Check if the topic has has_draft=1. IF so, read and return its draft content.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.approveDraft(topicName) -> Topic
  CALLS: KodexManager.getTopic (kodex-manager), KodexManager.updateFlagStatus (kodex-manager)
  Copy all draft content files over the live content files. Delete the draft/ directory.
  Set has_draft=0. Auto-resolve all open flags for the topic. Return the updated topic.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.rejectDraft(topicName) -> void
  Delete the draft/ directory. Set has_draft=0.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.listFlags(status) -> Flag[]
  Query flags, optionally filtered by status, ordered by created_at descending.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.hasFlag(topicName, type) -> boolean
  Check open flags for a matching topicName + type combination.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.createFlag(topicName, type, description, options) -> { created, reason }
  CALLS: KodexManager.hasFlag (kodex-manager)
  IF dedupe is enabled, check for an existing open flag of the same type; skip if found.
  Optionally append context to the description. Insert the flag row.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.updateFlagStatus(id, status) -> void
  Update flag status and set resolved_at (null if reopening, current time otherwise).

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.logAccess(topicName, source, context) -> void
  Insert a row into access_log. Upsert access_counts to increment count and update last_accessed.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.logMissing(topicName, context) -> void
  Upsert missing_topics to increment count and update requested_at.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.getDashboardStats() -> DashboardStats
  Query counts for total topics, verified topics, pending drafts, and open flags.
  Fetch the 10 most recent access log entries and the 10 most-requested missing topics.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.getMissingTopics() -> MissingTopicEntry[]
  Return all missing_topics rows ordered by count descending.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.readTopicContent(name) -> TopicContent
  Read all five content files from the topic's live directory.
  Pass diagrams.md through resolveDiagramLinks before returning.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.readDraftContent(name) -> TopicContent
  Read all five content files from the topic's draft/ directory.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.resolveDiagramLinks(content, topicDir) -> string
  For each line in content that matches a markdown link to a .mmd file, replace the
  link with a ### heading, optional description, and a fenced mermaid code block
  containing the file's contents. Lines that don't match are passed through unchanged.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.readFileOrEmpty(path) -> string
  Return file contents if the file exists, otherwise return an empty string.

---

FUNCTION KodexManager.close() -> void
  Close the SQLite database and null out the reference.

---

FUNCTION getKodexManager(projectPath) -> KodexManager                             EXPORT
  Return a cached KodexManager for the given project path, creating one if needed.
